Sales Director Job (Information Technology) Jakarta, Indonesia  -
Sales Director Job (Information Technology) Jakarta, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Our client is a large multinational company from the U.S., with several divisions and a focal division in network powers. This company division specialises in the development and manufacturing of power supplies, power backup generators, computing solutions, data center infrastructure management, precision cooling, original equipment manufacturers, and technologies for telecommunications service providers, industrial facilities and IT health care professionals. Our highly-respected client are seeking a new key position of Sales Director to lead and guide the overall direction and growth in Jakarta, Indonesia Main responsibilities: Map Market by segmentsDevelop Strategic Market penetration plansGuide and motivate account managers to achieve personal sales and margin targets and in the process, meet or exceed company’s sales and margin targetsKeep track of sales activities and Account Managers’ performance against their objectives.Assist Account Managers in their duties and facilitate their activities so that customer’s enquiries are satisfied.Act as an interface or liaison between the world-wide ENP factories and local Account Managers on matters related to the factories and products.Meet with potential clients to explain proposals and solutions in order to secure the sales away from the competitorConduct product presentations to clients and users and be able to impart the knowledge on our product strengths and applications and how they meet the requirements of our clientsSubmit Sales forecast, project tracking reports, won/lost/pending reports and all other reports related to sales activities and projects as required by managementDefend and increase market share by following the activities of the competition and develop strategies to compete aggressively in the marketMaintain and defend our customer base by ensuring accounts assigned are properly maintained and serviced.Train and motivate Account Managers to ensure they have the necessary skills and knowledge to represent the company on the product range.Co-ordinate with Supply Chain to identify sub-contractors on supply of third party products and services to meet project budget and maximise profitability.Ensure our customers and clients have full customer satisfactions when they deal with Emerson Network Power.Keep abreast of activities and changes in the industry and develop sales strategies to counteract any negative impact on our business. Job requirements: Solid business acumen, at least basic knowledge of a P&LDegree in Electrical, Mechanical, Industrial or Electro-mechanical engineering or Equivalent. Having a MBA would be advantageous.Minimal 15 years’ experience in Technical or System Sales experience with good track recordGood verbal and written communication skillsGood Presentation SkillsPrevious experience with a multinational companyExperience managing a Sales Organization All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to technology@monroeconsulting.com
